snippet: Officials and analysts say that the ruble’s nose dive has put pressure on the Russian president to take a more flexible position on Ukraine.
abstract: Analysts say upheaval in Russian economy may be pushing Russian Pres Vladimir V Putin to seek compromise in crisis over Ukraine, though he has proved so erratic that progress is difficult to gauge.

byline.contributor: Neil MacFarquhar contributed reporting from Moscow, Andrew Higgins from Brussels and Victor Homola from Berlin.

lead_paragraph: Officials and analysts say that the ruble’s nose dive has put pressure on the Russian president to take a more flexible position on Ukraine.

headline.main: Economic Fears May Push Russia Into Ukraine Deal
headline.print_headline: Economic Fears May Push Russia Into Ukraine Deal
